translated: Ekstedt, Knut Olof (Olle), district prosecutor, Mariannelund, born on June 26, 1899 in Enköping to iron merchant Axel E. and AHce Bildt. Married in 1931 to pharmacist Elsa Lind-berger. Completed secondary school exam in Stockholm in 1919, appointed district prosecutor in Uppsala in 1926, and has been district prosecutor in Mariannelunds since 1941. Member of the municipal council in Mariannelunds town. Enjoys hunting as a hobby and has received the Royal Swedish Academy of Agriculture and Forestry's silver medal for merit.
